# For Active Accounts
You can simply renew domain from Server Point client portal. Use the following procedure
1. Go to https://www.serverpointapps.com. Then click on Client Portal. 
2. Click on the Menu , then go Domain names and you will see a list of your domains and expiration dates. 
3. Click on the domain name you want to renew.
4. Click on the "Action" Tab >> Then click to "Renew" button to renew the domain. Domain name can be renewed for a maximum of 9 years of renewal

The payments will be processed from the credit card or from the account fund

# For canceled accounts
Now domain can be renewed using the New ClientPortal even though the account is already cancelled and there is no active hosting account. You can use the same steps mentioned above for Active Accounts.

# Procedures to Renew a Domain if its not listing in Control Panel

If a customer want to renew a domain and its not listing in control panel, then check the following

    First do the following command to confirm the domain registered with us and for the current status

     whois domain.com 

    Check the is active or not. If its not cancelled, then do the above cancelled account procedure.
    If its cancelled resold account, but the main account is active, then contact Minerva to add the resold domain to the main account control panel
    If the domain is not listing in ICP, but its registered with us, then check his main account or ask the customer about his active account. Then contact Minerva . She can add it if the domain exist in the data base. If it is not existing then prepare the Query and send it Minerva
    If the domain and account name list in ICP, then contact Minerva, she can add it easily.

# If client didn't receive domain renewal notification due to wrong Admin EMail address

Reply:
We really apologize for the inconveniance you have faced.

Your domain's admin email address is <put domain Admin Email address here >, Several emails were sent at that email address. 

 - 60 Days domain expiry notice 
 - 30 Days domain expiry notice 
 - 15 Days domain expiry notice 
 - 5 Days domain deactivation warning 
 - 24 hours domain deactivation warning  

When domain is expired then email stop working, As soon as your domain will be renewed, Your email will automatically start working. 

Please make sure your admin contact is updated so that you dont face this problem in future. You can also renew your domain for mutiple years to avoid such problem.
  
  
  
# Domain in Redemption Period
>   Redemption
> 
> Max Limit of redemption period is 70 day after expiration date
> 
> The domain exceed the limit, then customer has to contact opensrs directly to renew this.
> 
> Check their policy from http://www.opensrs.com/docs/opensrsrwi/expired_domains.htm

 Reply: 
  Your domain is in redemption period. Several alerts were sent but we never hear from you.
It has now passed its expiry period and now fallen in redemption.

If your domain enters such period, the registrar will require a $120 payment to recover the domain.

Redemption period is the Grace Period of the domain for 30 days. Whois information (name, address, telephone numbers, etc.) will be deleted. The domain 
will still be inactive. The domain may be renewed by it's original owner for a very high fee. It is a manual process for the registry to add the 
name/address information back into the domain registry records, therefore, the process may take several days.

Five days after the end of the redemption period the domain name will be deleted from the registry and will be made available for anyone to register.

Remember that decisions made by the domain's registrar, the company that handles your domain on the global Internet, is not the responsibility of your host.

If you wish to get your domain out of redemption period, contact us asap.
